usestate is used to update the current value	

syntax  ==> const[state,setState]

state => current value (or) initial value

setState => updating value

example  ==> const[num , setNum] = useState(0) ==> here 0 is the current/initial value

too many renders error will pop up if we call a function with parenthesis

and in onClick C should be caps
